To implement the **RCM Study Manager**, I will create a sidebar to manage saved studies, update the main application logic to handle saving/loading from local storage, and integrate a "Save" button into the results toolbar.

Here is the plan:
1.  **`types.ts`**: Add the `SavedStudy` interface.
2.  **`components/Sidebar.tsx`**: Create a new component to list, load, and delete studies.
3.  **`components/AnalysisResult.tsx`**: Add a "Save Study" button to the main toolbar.
4.  **`App.tsx`**: Implement the storage logic, integrate the sidebar, and manage the study lifecycle.

# Updated files:

## types.ts

Added `SavedStudy` interface to define the structure of a saved analysis.

```typescript
export interface InspectionSheet {
  checkPointDescription: string;
  type: 'Qualitative' | 'Quantitative';
  estimatedTime: string;
  normalCondition: string;
}

export interface RCMItem {
  id: string;
  component: string;
  function: string;
  functionalFailure: string;
  failureMode: string;
  failureEffect: string;
  criticality: 'High' | 'Medium' | 'Low';
  maintenanceTask: string;
  interval: string;
  taskType: 'Condition Monitoring' | 'Time-Based' | 'Run-to-Failure' | 'Redesign';
  inspectionSheet?: InspectionSheet;
}

export interface AnalysisStats {
  totalItems: number;
  highRisk: number;
  mediumRisk: number;
  lowRisk: number;
}

export type InputMode = 'manual' | 'upload';

export interface FileData {
  name: string;
  mimeType: string;
  data: string; // base64
}

export interface SavedStudy {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  timestamp: number;
  items: RCMItem[];
  contextText: string;
  fileName?: string; // We store reference to file, but maybe not the heavy base64 to save localStorage space
}
```

To provide a quick reference for the Severity, Occurrence, and Detection (SOD) scoring criteria, I will create a new **Reference Guide Modal**.

1.  **New Component (`components/SODReference.tsx`)**: This will contain the industry-standard FMECA scoring tables (1-10 scale) for all three factors. I've designed it with a tabbed interface so you can easily switch between Severity, Occurrence, and Detection definitions without clutter.
2.  **Update Header (`App.tsx`)**: I will add a "Reference Book" button next to the Save button. Clicking this instantly opens the scoring guide popup.

